## Introduction to Math-Magic: The Story of the Camels
ଓଡ଼ିଆ: ଏହି ପାଠରେ ଆମେ ଗଣିତର ଯାଦୁ ବିଷୟରେ ଶିଖିବା, ଯେଉଁଠି ଜଣେ ବୁଦ୍ଧିମାନ ଯୁବକ କିପରି ଉଟମାନଙ୍କୁ ଭାଗ କରିବାର ଏକ କଷ୍ଟକର ସମସ୍ୟାକୁ ସମାଧାନ କଲେ।
This lesson introduces us to a fascinating story from the chapter "Math-Magic." It demonstrates how a clever application of mathematics can solve seemingly impossible problems. We will explore the tale of three brothers, their inheritance, and the ingenious solution provided by a young math-man.

## The Problem of Inheritance
ଓଡ଼ିଆ: ତିନି ଭାଇ ତାଙ୍କ ପିତାଙ୍କ ଇଚ୍ଛାପତ୍ର ଅନୁଯାୟୀ ୩୫ଟି ଓଟକୁ ଭାଗ କରିବାକୁ ଚେଷ୍ଟା କରୁଥିଲେ, କିନ୍ତୁ ଏହା କଷ୍ଟକର ଥିଲା କାରଣ ଭାଗଗୁଡ଼ିକ ଭଗ୍ନାଂଶରେ ଥିଲା।
Once, three brothers were found quarrelling (କଳି) over their inheritance (ଉତ୍ତରାଧିକାର). Their father had passed away, leaving behind a will (ଇଚ୍ଛାପତ୍ର) and thirty-five camels. According to the will, the eldest (ବଡ଼) son was to receive $rac{1}{2}$ of the camels, the second (ଦ୍ୱିତୀୟ) son $rac{1}{3}$, and the youngest (ସାନ) son $rac{1}{9}$.

However, dividing thirty-five camels according to these fractional shares proved difficult (କଷ୍ଟକର). Let's look at the initial calculations:
*   Eldest son: $rac{1}{2}  imes 35 = 17.5$ camels
*   Second son: $rac{1}{3}  imes 35  approx 11.67$ camels
*   Youngest son: $rac{1}{9}  imes 35  approx 3.89$ camels

It is impossible to divide a living camel into halves or other fractions, leading to the brothers' dispute.

## The Ingenious Solution
ଓଡ଼ିଆ: ଜଣେ ଯୁବକ ତାଙ୍କର ନିଜ ଓଟକୁ ୩୫ଟି ଓଟ ସହିତ ମିଶାଇଲେ, ଯାହାଦ୍ୱାରା ମୋଟ ଓଟ ସଂଖ୍ୟା ୩୬ ହେଲା ଏବଂ ଭାଗ କରିବା ସହଜ ହେଲା।
A young math-man, observing their predicament, offered a solution. He simply added (ଯୋଡ଼ିଲେ) his own camel to their herd (ପଲ). This increased the total (ମୋଟ) number of camels from 35 to 36. This clever step transformed the problem into an easily solvable one.

Let's recalculate the shares with 36 camels:
*   Eldest son: $rac{1}{2}  imes 36 = 18$ camels
*   Second son: $rac{1}{3}  imes 36 = 12$ camels
*   Youngest son: $rac{1}{9}  imes 36 = 4$ camels

Each brother received a whole number of camels, making them all happy (ଖୁସି).

## The Math-Magic Revealed
ଓଡ଼ିଆ: ଓଟ ବଣ୍ଟା ହେବା ପରେ, ମୋଟ ୩୪ଟି ଓଟ ବଣ୍ଟା ହେଲା ଏବଂ ଯୁବକଙ୍କର ନିଜ ଓଟ ସହିତ ଆଉ ଗୋଟିଏ ଓଟ ବଳିଲା, ଯାହା ଗଣିତର ଯାଦୁ ଦେଖାଇଲା।
After the distribution, let's sum the camels received by the brothers:
$18 + 12 + 4 = 34$ camels.

Surprisingly, only 34 camels were distributed out of the 36 available! This meant that the young math-man not only got his own camel back but also found an extra camel. He had no camel of his own initially but gained (ଲାଭ କଲେ) one by solving their problem. This is the true "magic (ଯାଦୁ) of knowing mathematics (ଗଣିତ)" – a solution that benefits everyone and seems to create something out of nothing.

